So, they refused to say, even though, as, as you know in the Quran, Abraham repeats, when he talks to his father, he keeps saying

983
01:22:12,263 --> 01:22:16,377
"oh my father, oh my father, oh my father, oh my father, Ya Abati (يَـٰٓأَبَتِ), Ya Abati (يَـٰٓأَبَتِ)."

984
01:22:18,377 --> 01:22:21,042
But God knew that they will do that.

985
01:22:23,042 --> 01:22:25,284
Not once did he say "Ya Ammi (یا عمي)", you know.

986
01:22:25,284 --> 01:22:27,284
Every time he said "Ya Abati (يَـٰٓأَبَتِ), Ya Abati (يَـٰٓأَبَتِ), Ya Abati (يَـٰٓأَبَتِ)."

987
01:22:27,284 --> 01:22:29,284
Dr. Khalifa: He never said "oh my uncle", once.

988
01:22:31,284 --> 01:22:33,767
A woman: (unintelligible)

989
01:22:34,492 --> 01:22:37,398
Dr. Khalifa: Right. According to this.

990
01:22:43,499 --> 01:22:47,251
Dr. Khalifa: Yeah, sometimes you look at the English to
understand the Arabic word, you know,

991
01:22:47,251 --> 01:22:54,594
because this Quranic Arabic, sometimes there
are words that are not used anymore in our

992
01:22:54,594 --> 01:22:57,104
regular Tunisian Arabic or Egyptian Arabic.

993
01:22:57,979 --> 01:23:02,241
So, if you go to the English, then we remember,
we know the meaning.

994
01:23:10,518 --> 01:23:11,518
Dr. Khalifa: That's okay.

995
01:23:15,626 --> 01:23:20,042
Edip: Rashad, a few days ago, we were reading Quran.

996
01:23:21,673 --> 01:23:24,458
Edip: We had a question about prostrating.

997
01:23:25,123 --> 01:23:30,264
Especially in Quran, I think there are some
different meanings.

998
01:23:30,264 --> 01:23:31,418
Edip: We have...
Dr. Khalifa: Submission.

999
01:23:31,780 --> 01:23:34,384
Edip: Submission, for example, God says,
Dr. Khalifa: Obedience.

1000
01:23:34,384 --> 01:23:36,625
Edip: Enter the city humbly,

1001
01:23:36,625 --> 01:23:37,236
(2:58) سُجَّدًا

1002
01:23:37,236 --> 01:23:40,625
Not prostrating. But Sujjadan (سُجَّدًا) means humbly.

1003
01:23:41,048 --> 01:23:45,948
Edip: Everything, creatures, they make Sujud, they prostrate God,
but in their way.

1004
01:23:45,948 --> 01:23:47,344
Dr. Khalifa: I never saw a tree go like this.

1005
01:23:47,344 --> 01:23:49,525
Edip: It means obey, obeying, obeying.

1006
01:23:49,525 --> 01:23:50,136
Dr. Khalifa: Submit

1007
01:23:50,136 --> 01:24:01,801
Edip: Yes, submission. And there is a word about, there's a verse about Joseph's parents and brothers, they fell prostrate for him.

1008
01:24:02,072 --> 01:24:10,623
It is, if you understand in this way that because only God,
we should prostrate only to God. How can we understand this?

1009
01:24:10,623 --> 01:24:12,019
It was a question.

1010
01:24:13,979 --> 01:24:17,275
Edip: How did they fell prostrate for Joseph?

1011
01:24:19,275 --> 01:24:20,127
Dr. Khalifa: Well,...

1012
01:24:20,127 --> 01:24:22,154
Edip: Like this way? Like this way?

1013
01:24:22,154 --> 01:24:24,335
Dr. Khalifa: No, Behrouz was worried about his brother.

1014
01:24:25,181 --> 01:24:29,597
And then, he called him by phone, and his brother
answered the phone, and everything was alright.

1015
01:24:29,597 --> 01:24:31,597
So, as soon as he finished, he fell prostrate.

1016
01:24:31,597 --> 01:24:33,597
Dr. Khalifa: He was really prostrating to God.
Edip: Ok.

1017
01:24:34,382 --> 01:24:36,926
Dr. Khalifa: So, the same...
Edip: I gave him the answer, but I was not sure.

1018
01:24:36,926 --> 01:24:40,980
Dr. Khalifa: When they met Joseph, they were so thankful
to God that they fell prostrate.

1019
01:24:41,584 --> 01:24:48,236
They did not feel prostrate to Joseph. They
fell prostrate before God, thanking him because

1020
01:24:48,236 --> 01:24:49,632
Dr. Khalifa: they are united with Joseph.

1021
01:24:49,632 --> 01:24:52,478
Edip: But the English translation, I think there
must be a correction.

1022
01:24:52,478 --> 01:24:57,740
Edip: "Before Joseph", instead of "for Joseph." If this
is "for Joseph", it's ok. This is my understanding.

1023
01:24:57,740 --> 01:25:03,546
Dr. Khalifa: This is what the Arabic said. But your understanding must be that they fell prostrate, thanking God.

1024
01:25:03,546 --> 01:25:05,908
He didn't fall prostrate for, for his brother.

1025
01:25:06,452 --> 01:25:10,265
He was prostrating to God and thanking God
that everything is ok. But the Arabic says,

1026
01:25:10,265 --> 01:25:11,600
(12:100) وَخَرُّوا۟ لَهُۥ سُجَّدًۭا

1027
01:25:11,902 --> 01:25:15,974
Edip:
وَخَرُّوا۟ لَهُۥ
(unintelligible)

1028
01:25:17,001 --> 01:25:18,034
Dr. Khalifa:
سُجَّدًا لله

1029
01:25:18,034 --> 01:25:19,732
Dr. Khalifa: Same, same expression.

1030
01:25:19,732 --> 01:25:20,886
Edip: Also, Rashad,...

1031
01:25:20,886 --> 01:25:25,269
Dr. Khalifa: So, but I'm, I'm translating the Arabic exactly the
way.

1032
01:25:25,549 --> 01:25:29,267
And if God wants some people to be confused
about it, that's their problem,

1033
01:25:29,267 --> 01:25:34,194
but you and I will understand that prostration
is only for God, not for humans.

1034
01:25:34,496 --> 01:25:41,718
Dr. Khalifa: There's a, there are some traps in the Quran for the
unbelievers.

1035
01:25:42,202 --> 01:25:46,766
Edip: And I think that this is a fulfillment of the dream.

1036
01:25:46,766 --> 01:25:47,618
Dr. Khalifa: Right.

1037
01:25:47,618 --> 01:25:53,001
Edip: In dream, sun, and all planets, no, no, all planets, they
are prostrating to sun.

1038
01:25:53,001 --> 01:25:54,095
Dr. Khalifa: No, no, no.

1039
01:25:54,095 --> 01:25:54,595
Edip: Yes.

1040
01:25:54,595 --> 01:25:56,293
Dr. Khalifa: The sun, the moon, and eleven planets

1041
01:25:56,293 --> 01:25:57,870
Edip: prostrating
Dr. Khalifa: to Joseph.

1042
01:25:57,870 --> 01:26:04,038
Edip: Joseph now, I think, represents sun because
all these planets, they turn around the sun. They...

1043
01:26:04,038 --> 01:26:09,119
Dr. Khalifa: No, the sun represents the father, the moon represents
the mother, and the eleven planets are his eleven brothers.

1044
01:26:10,750 --> 01:26:13,596
Dr. Khalifa: They were all prostrating to Joseph.
Edip: Oh, oh, yes.

1045
01:26:14,442 --> 01:26:20,489
Dr. Khalifa: This is, in fact, this is in the books of
dream interpretations in the Arab world.

1046
01:26:20,489 --> 01:26:26,597
Dr. Khalifa: The sun means the father and the moon means
the mother, and so on. And they take it from this.

1047
01:26:27,382 --> 01:26:29,382
A man: But in the next verse, he says,...

1048
01:26:29,382 --> 01:26:31,080
Edip: (unintelligible) Yes.

1049
01:26:31,080 --> 01:26:31,811
Dr. Khalifa: Pardon?

1050
01:26:31,811 --> 01:26:33,086
Edip: Maybe earth.

1051
01:26:33,811 --> 01:26:37,080
Dr. Khalifa: No, maybe nothing, he's just Joseph. Just in the dream.

1052
01:26:37,568 --> 01:26:43,703
Dr. Khalifa: A dream can have many representations. What is seven fat cows eating seven skinny cows? Or vice versa.

1053
01:26:43,703 --> 01:26:46,005
A man: So, he's telling him "don't tell your brothers."

1054
01:26:46,005 --> 01:26:48,428
[12:5]  ... Surely, the devil is man's worst enemy.

1055
01:26:48,428 --> 01:26:49,280
Dr. Khalifa: Yes.

1056
01:26:49,280 --> 01:26:50,005
A man: So, we see...

1057
01:26:50,005 --> 01:26:55,355
Dr. Khalifa: Because the devil will stir up his brothers
against him. The devil drives wedges among the brothers.

1058
01:26:57,167 --> 01:27:00,281
Dr. Khalifa: Okay. Next time we'll meet at seven o'clock, IN SHAA ALLAH.

1059
01:27:00,281 --> 01:27:01,616
A man: IN SHAA ALLAH.

1060
01:27:02,886 --> 01:27:06,302
Dr. Khalifa: For the Night Prayer. Salat Al-Isha.

1061
01:27:10,712 --> 01:27:15,000
If you miss, if you miss the Night
Prayer, we meet at six o'clock in the morning for the Fajr Prayer.

1062
01:27:31,190 --> 01:27:32,163
Dr. Khalifa: 286.

1063
01:27:35,063 --> 01:27:37,063
A woman: 296 or 86?
A man: 86.

1064
01:27:37,063 --> 01:27:38,096
Dr. Khalifa: 286.

1065
01:28:04,608 --> 01:28:07,695
Dr. Khalifa: Thank you, Muhammad. We're waiting for you.

1066
01:28:09,266 --> 01:28:10,360
IN SHAA ALLAH.

1067
01:28:17,000 --> 01:28:20,329
أعوذ بِٱللَّهِ مِنَ ٱلشَّيْطَـٰنِ ٱلرَّجِيمِ
